Each chiropractor member of the Board shall be:
A resident of this State;
A licensed chiropractor of integrity and ability who is in active practice;
A graduate of a resident course in chiropractic; and
An individual who has practiced chiropractic in this State for at least 5 consecutive years.

Each massage therapist member of the Board shall be:
A resident of this State;
A licensed massage therapist of integrity and ability who is in active practice;
A graduate of a Board-approved course in massage therapy; and
An individual who has practiced massage therapy in this State for at least 5 consecutive years.

Each consumer member of the Board:
Shall be a member of the general public;
May not be or ever have been a chiropractor or massage therapist or in training to become a chiropractor or massage therapist;
May not have a household member who is a chiropractor or massage therapist or in training to become a chiropractor or massage therapist;
May not participate or ever have participated in a commercial or professional field related to chiropractic or massage therapy;
May not have a household member who participates in a commercial or professional field related to chiropractic or massage therapy; and
May not have had, within 2 years before appointment, a substantial financial interest in a person regulated by the Board.
